 The Pacific Ocean.
The Pacific Ocean covers one-third of the surface area of our planet. It contains more than half of all water in the world’s oceans and seas. This vast body of saltwater has a circumference of about 25,000 miles (40,000 km). The Pacific basin extends from Antarctica to Alaska at its widest point.
